com.pump.animation.writing

Class WritingStroke

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pump.animation.writing.WritingStroke
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class WritingStroke
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    A single segment of a hand-drawn graphic. This includes a path to trace and a pause.

    The pause measured in "beats", which are an arbitrary construct. (And they can be accelerated or decelerated, just like the writing rate.) A pause beat should correspond to the amount of time used to leave a space between words. So if that corresponds to a unit of 1, then you might want to add a pause of length .05 or .1 when you lift up your pen and write the straight line in a "Q". Or you might put a pause of .25 or .5 when writing the three dots an ellipses.

        public WritingStroke deriveWStroke(float newPauseBeats)
